Title: The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes
Author: Arthur Conan Doyle
My Review: pretty fun readthrough, but not entirely my vibe. the 1880s london setting is AWESOME, and maybe the most interesting draw- doyle really lets a reader in on everything about it. the perfect atmosphere for detective stories... smoky, serious, and almost cartoonishly Victorian. however, some of the mysteries (especially toward the middle) felt a bit contrived, and it got kinda hard to read through.
